#30026
Preparing Spells for Casting By Memorizing Them~
   In order for some classes to cast spells, they must memorize the spells
first.  Currently those classes are mages, clerics, druids, paladins and
rangers.  To memorize a spell, first confirm that you have the spell with the
spells command, or by checking your spellbook if you are a wizard.  Then the
command to memorize the spell is @Ymem <spellcasting class>
<spell-name-with-dashes-like-this>@n.  For example 'mem mage magic-missile'.  To
stop a spell that is in the process of being memorized, use the @Ystop@n command
using the same syntax as the mem command.  To forget a memorized spell use the
@Yforget@n command using the same syntax.  You can view the spells you have
memorized and are memorizing by typing @Ymem <spellcasting class>@n.  For
example 'mem mage' will show all of the mage spells you have memorized and are
memorizing.  Normally you will automatically rememorize spells that you cast,
but if you wish to toggle this option on and off, simply type @Yautomem@n.  
