The Formation System~
   D20MUD uses a formation system.  There are two main commands associated with
this system: @YFORM@n and @YREFORM@n.  Generally, the formation system can allow
for groups of up to 16 people, with up to 4 front line melee fighters, 4 second
row fighters, and 4 third row fighters.  Those in row 1, can attack using any
weapon.  Those in row 2 must use either polearms or ranged weapons.  Those in
row 3 must use ranged weapons only.  You may cast spells from any row.  To see
your party's current formation type form.  To change your own position type
'reform self <position number'.  So if I wanted to put myself in melee range,
and slot 3 was open, I would type 'reform self 3'.  Only those in row 1 are able
to be attacked by mobs most of the time.  
