#30031
Consider Your Enemy~

Before you attack anything you haven't fought before, you will want to
consider it.  For your convenience we have added an autocon system as well.
To manually consider your enemy type @Yconsider <target>@n.  It will give you
a message detailing how powerful the creature is compared to you.  The autocon
system on the other hand, which is turned on by default, places a symbol in
parenthesis beside the mob's long description.  It will also display a
color code.  Here is a quick legend:
@B(+)@n 8 levels lower than yours or more
@b(+)@n 7 levels lower than yours
@C(-)@n 6 levels lower than yours
@c(-)@n 5 levels lower than yours
@G(-)@n 4 levels lower than yours
@g(-)@n 3 levels lower than yours
@Y(-)@n 2 levels lower than yours
@y(-)@n 1 level lower than yours
@W(=)@n same level as yours
@m(+)@n 1 level higher than yours
@M(+)@n 2 levels higher than yours
@r(+)@n 3 levels higher than yours
@R(+)@n 4 levels higher than yours
@l@R(+)@n 5 levels higher than yours or more
@W(==)@n double normal hit points
