#30032
Religion, Devotion and Domains~
   WIn the world of Krynn, everyone must devote themselves to one of the deities
to give principle worship to (though many people revere multiple dieities).  
Those who do not devote themselves to a deity, or who only pay lip service to
their deity, are given to Chemosh to do with as he wills, which often results in
the soul haunting the world as undead, or acting as an eternal slave.  Thus the
people of Krynn take their religion quite seriously, and virtually every
sentient creature on the planet worships at least one deity.  For divine
spellcasters, this is even more important, for they can cast no spells without a
patron deity.  In order to choose a deity, type devote <deity name>.  To see a
list of deities which you qualify to be accepted as a worshipper, type 'devote
list'.  If you are a cleric you may choose up to two domains of the four that
your deity possess.  These domains will grant you bonus spells and bonus
abilities (in most cases).  To see a list of domains your deity offers type
'domain'.  If you have not yet devoted to a deity, the game will, at this point,
direct you to do so.  To see what benefits a domain offers, type 'help domain
<domain name>'.  Once you have chosen your two domains, you can see what they
are at any time by typing 'domain' by itself.  @RIf you do not devote to a deity
you will suffer greater experience penalties when you die.  @n
